commit_message:
Simplify path for letsencrypt usage

Adding required parameters into horizon service will allow deployers not to
maintain their own versions of haproxy_default_services,
and we can simply add letsencrypt service when
haproxy_ssl_letsencrypt_enable is true.

Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/751316
Change-Id: I4f9f8d9d9fc0ec8c57a3e1e7dda49ccea8cda388
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/openstack-ansible refs/changes/27/751327/3 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: --- upgrade: - | There's no need in keeping `letsencrypt` service in haproxy_extra_services as well as copying and maintaining whole haproxy_default_services in order to get overrides for horizon. From now on required adjustments are provided by defualt and letsecrypt installation path has been simplified.

commit_message:
Blacklist etcd3gw 0.2.6

etcd3gw 0.2.6 was blacklisted in openstack/requirements [0], because
that version has a bug [1].

tooz does not use openstack/requirements' upper constraints, so the
same blacklisting needs to be introduced here in setup.cfg.

[0] Icb6873d8c5d3a3624c0ac3d76fc9125c5d8134b2
[1] https://github.com/dims/etcd3-gateway/issues/41

Change-Id: I22b955419014dd34c63e406c488e0636ffe9013b

Configure swap as before

high failure rate of the functional and grenade jobs.

commit_message:
Do not manage /etc/ssl or /etc/pki directories or symlinks

For a metal deployment the keystone and horizon roles both try to
do this and it should be done in one place. This is moved to the
openstack_hosts role.

Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/754095
Depends-On: https://review.opendev.org/754382

commit_message:
Performance: use import_tasks for register and bootstrap

Including tasks has a performance penalty when compared with importing
tasks. If the include has a condition associated with it, then the
overhead of the include may be lower than the overhead of skipping all
imported tasks. In the case of the register.yml and bootstrap.yml
includes, all of the tasks in the included file use run_once: True.
The run_once flag improves performance at scale drastically, so
importing these tasks unconditionally will have a lower overhead than a
conditional include task.  It therefore makes sense to switch to use
import_tasks there.

See [1] for benchmarks of run_once.

[1] https://github.com/stackhpc/ansible-scaling/blob/master/doc/run-once.md

Change-Id: Ic67631ca3ea3fb2081a6f8978e85b1522522d40d
Partially-Implements: blueprint performance-improvements
(cherry picked from commit 496904d650d340cd78fd0bd3f1863a38e6661633)

commit_message:
Use upper constraints when installing Bifrost requirements

Currently the install-deps.sh script installs Bifrost's Python
requirements without upper constraints. This can result in requirements
drifting over time, with issues arising in older branches.

This change fixes the issue by using an upper constraints to install
Bifrost's requirements.

Change-Id: Icf66d0faf77837b9b48df344578823e46017b1df
(cherry picked from commit b6624b2dbee6134be8e1db18b49cfd0228429021)

commit_message:
optimize size and time using --no-cache-dir

Using --no-cache-dir flag in pip install ,make sure dowloaded packages
by pip don't cached on system . This is a best practise which make sure
to fetch ftom repo instead of using local cached one . Further , in case
of Docker Containers , by restricing caching , we can reduce image size.
In term of stats , it depends upon the number of python packages
multiplied by their respective size . e.g for heavy packages with a lot
of dependencies it reduce a lot by don't caching pip packages.

Further , more detail information can be found at

https://medium.com/sciforce/strategies-of-docker-images-optimization-2ca9cc5719b6

Change-Id: If206e41f3bac6e0b73b57e85c80fa2530ee9d4cf
Signed-off-by: Pratik Raj <rajpratik71@gmail.com>

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2020-10-07 05:01:31.000000000', 'files': ['paunch/utils/systemd.py'], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/paunch/commit/cca61e69995676efe08a05536ffb76b07091255c', 'message': 'Instruct systemd to accept 137 and 143 exit code

It might happen a container takes time to stop its running process - it
therefore will call "SIGTERM" or "SIGKILL", and conmon will return the
actual process exit code.
Since the exit code won't be 0, it will be marked as "failed" in systemd
status.

Note that 137 is, actually, SIGKILL (137-128 = 9) and 143 is SIGTERM
(143-128 = 15).

another one will be created against triple-ansible.

commit_message:
Instruct systemd to accept 137 and 143 exit code

It might happen a container takes time to stop its running process - it
therefore will call "SIGTERM" or "SIGKILL", and conmon will return the
actual process exit code.
Since the exit code won't be 0, it will be marked as "failed" in systemd
status.

Note that 137 is, actually, SIGKILL (137-128 = 9) and 143 is SIGTERM
(143-128 = 15).
While systemd accepts actual SIGTERM by default, it doesn't recognize that
143 exit status. We therefore have to namely point to this status code.
Also, by default, SIGKILL isn't accepted as a valid, successful exit status.

This change will needs to be backported down to stable/train - and
another one will be created against triple-ansible.

Change-Id: Iffcfc8bd18a999ae6921a4131d40241df40050f1
(cherry picked from commit c19a95d2eb778662ba342ff5e6a966ec632687a4)

commit_message:
Remove "when" statement from vars_prompt

In ansible 2.10 when statement is not supported for vars_prompt.
Also default behaviour will not ask for vars_prompt in case var is passed
with -e or in non-interactive shell [1]

[1] https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/user_guide/playbooks_prompts.html

Change-Id: I1fcb7d195139b82edfa17eba43a4ef9b6256297f

Remove the deperecated parameter/resource about api-paste.ini

because they were already deprecated in the previous cycle[1].

added_lines: @decorators.idempotent_id('85c1bbd0-da1f-4b7e-9ac0-4a53cd51c314') def test_amphora_delete(self): """Tests amphora delete API. * delete amphora. * Validate the amphora delete successful. * Validates that non-admin accounts cannot delete amphora. """ lb_name = data_utils.rand_name("lb_member_lb3_amphora-list") lb = self.mem_lb_client.create_loadbalancer( name=lb_name, provider=CONF.load_balancer.provider, vip_network_id=self.lb_member_vip_net[const.ID]) lb_id = lb[const.ID] self.addCleanup(self.mem_lb_client.cleanup_loadbalancer, lb_id) waiters.wait_for_status(self.mem_lb_client.show_loadbalancer, lb_id, const.PROVISIONING_STATUS, const.ACTIVE, CONF.load_balancer.lb_build_interval, CONF.load_balancer.lb_build_timeout) # Get an actual list of the amphorae amphorae = self.lb_admin_amphora_client.list_amphorae( query_params='{loadbalancer_id}={lb_id}'.format( loadbalancer_id=const.LOADBALANCER_ID, lb_id=lb_id)) # Test that that non-admin accounts cannot delete amphora if CONF.load_balancer.RBAC_test_type == const.ADVANCED: self.assertRaises( exceptions.Forbidden, self.os_primary.amphora_client.delete_amphora, amphorae[0][const.ID]) for amp in amphorae: self.lb_admin_amphora_client.delete_amphora(amp[const.ID]) # Assert that amphora delete successful amphorae_2 = self.lb_admin_amphora_client.list_amphorae() self.assertNotIn(amp[const.ID], [it[const.ID] for it in amphorae_2])

subject: Handle libvirt reporting incorrect 4k page quantities
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2019-01-15 18:06:04.000000000', 'files': [], 'web_link': 'https://opendev.org/openstack/nova/commit/d253fa3d5554e0064a86c54455f3d7443f5f906d', 'message': "Handle libvirt reporting incorrect 4k page quantities

libvirt < 4.3.0 had an issue whereby assigning more than 4 GB of huge
pages would result in an incorrect value for the number of 4k (small)
pages [1]. This was fixed in 4.3.0 and the fixes appear to have been
backported to the libvirt versions for RHEL 7.4+.  However, this is
still an issue with the versions of libvirt available on Ubuntu 16.04,
18.04 and who knows what else. Work around the issue using the rest of
the (correct) values for different page sizes and warn the user so they
know what's going on.

[1] https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1569678

Change-Id: I28a7222d3ab80bb05e10caf753b4e78be2603c30

commit_message:
Handle libvirt reporting incorrect 4k page quantities

libvirt < 4.3.0 had an issue whereby assigning more than 4 GB of huge
pages would result in an incorrect value for the number of 4k (small)
pages [1]. This was fixed in 4.3.0 and the fixes appear to have been
backported to the libvirt versions for RHEL 7.4+.  However, this is
still an issue with the versions of libvirt available on Ubuntu 16.04,
18.04 and who knows what else. Work around the issue using the rest of
the (correct) values for different page sizes and warn the user so they
know what's going on.

[1] https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1569678

Change-Id: I28a7222d3ab80bb05e10caf753b4e78be2603c30
Signed-off-by: Stephen Finucane <sfinucan@redhat.com>
Closes-Bug: #1811870

added_lines: @ddt.unpack @ddt.data((False, False), (False, True), (True, False)) @mock.patch('nova.virt.libvirt.driver.LOG.warning') def test_get_host_numa_topology_broken_libvirt_meminfo(self, has_min_version, wrong_qty, mock_warning): """Ensure we correctly handle issues with libvirt < 4.3.0. libvirt < 4.3.0 reported incorrect values for small pages. We need to work around this. Ensure that happens. See bug #1811870 for more info. https://bugs.launchpad.net/nova/+bug/1811870 """ caps = vconfig.LibvirtConfigCaps() caps.host = vconfig.LibvirtConfigCapsHost() caps.host.cpu = vconfig.LibvirtConfigCPU() caps.host.cpu.arch = fields.Architecture.X86_64 caps.host.topology = fakelibvirt.NUMATopology() for i, cell in enumerate(caps.host.topology.cells): cell.memory = 16298528 # ~ 16 GiB # the incorrect values below were taken from a real-world system page_qty = 3075208 if wrong_qty else 2026632 cell.mempages = fakelibvirt.create_mempages( [(4, page_qty), (2048, 4000), (1048576, 0)]) drvr = libvirt_driver.LibvirtDriver(fake.FakeVirtAPI(), False) version = versionutils.convert_version_to_int( libvirt_driver.MIN_LIBVIRT_SMALL_PAGES) if not has_min_version: version -= 1 with test.nested( mock.patch.object( host.Host, 'get_capabilities', return_value=caps), mock.patch.object( hardware, 'get_vcpu_pin_set', return_value=set([0, 1, 3, 4, 5])), mock.patch.object( host.Host, 'get_online_cpus', return_value=set([0, 1, 2, 3, 6])), mock.patch.object( fakelibvirt.Connection, 'getLibVersion', return_value=version), ): got_topo = drvr._get_host_numa_topology() # in all cases the page counts must be accurate for cell in got_topo.cells: # the 4k pages total should always return 2026632 pages self.assertEqual(4, cell.mempages[0].size_kb) self.assertEqual(2026632, cell.mempages[0].total) self.assertEqual(2048, cell.mempages[1].size_kb) self.assertEqual(4000, cell.mempages[1].total) self.assertEqual(1048576, cell.mempages[2].size_kb) self.assertEqual(0, cell.mempages[2].total) # however the logs are only shown if the libvirt-provided value was # incorrect if not has_min_version and wrong_qty: self.assertTrue(mock_warning.called) else: self.assertFalse(mock_warning.called)

commit_message:
Allow to proceed with role if ceph_conf_file is set

We shouldn't stop role execution if ceph_mons is an epty list, since
deployer can provide ceph_conf_file and keys instead.

Change-Id: I35b23e266aa9c5e29e79ea040994039e47242c9c

commit_message:
exception cause stale flow cleaned but new flow not installed

rpc_loop 1:
physical bridge was just re-created, set bridges_recreated=True
set need_clean_stale_flow=True, process_network_ports argument
provisioning_needed is True but throw exception, not call
provision_local_vlan and flag need_clean_stale_flow keep True
rpc_loop 2:
set bridges_recreated=False process_network_ports argument
provisioning_needed is False, and not call provision_local_vlan.
Cleaning stale flows and set need_clean_stale_flow = False
so flow lost

Change-Id: I299174dbb5b74e9038c25bb8ff2e2c5b77b2fe28
Closes-Bug: #1881556

commit_message:
two pcs has same fc, del one pc del the other's db

two port chains have the same flowclassifier, flowclassifier
will create one row in portdetail, del one port chain,
port detail will be del, automaticaly del portpathasso.
del the other port chain, would not find portpathasso,
agent will not recive del flow rule message, ovs flow remained.

Change-Id: Icef605f78d7521a7a7d03363082bf47b90ea9902

commit_message:
Fix the ironic functional job

This change provides two workarounds:
* Disable dstat in devstack jobs, it's not compatible with Focal
* Do not use environment variables to select tests, the infra
  jobs no longer support tox_environment.

Change-Id: I765046781dca63e77dd7cf53a2d3e54f11e097d6

Reuse the docs deps to benefit from constraints

This ps to reuse upper-constraints.txt from docs deps

commit_message:
Remove mistral lines from scenario003 CI env

Master promotion jobs are failing because:
Service mistral_executor has not started yet.

This patch removes the Mistral related rservices
from the resource regsitry in the scenario003
CI env file.

Passed test job:
https://review.rdoproject.org/zuul/build/09f8a794d27242f88e4b9f8bced0c21c

Closes-Bug: #1898931
Change-Id: Ia0827b12cf44eb1c085a1d137e27489bcb959dec

commit_message:
Force CephAnsiblePlaybook to its default value on FFU prepare

There is code in tripleo-ansible [1] which will look at if user
customized the CephAnsiblePlaybook to run and, if so, will always
use that instead of the special playbook we intend to use on
_systemd or _fstobs tags.

This change will reset param value to its default on FFU
prepare so that we actually trigger the special playbooks later
on in the process, whichever custom setting operators might
have set via CephAnsiblePlaybook param for their Queens deployment.

Closes-Bug: 1898589

1. https://github.com/openstack/tripleo-ansible/blob/master/tripleo_ansible/roles/tripleo_ceph_run_ansible/tasks/main.yml#L19

Change-Id: If3c0e12181bb926125eb8aa1014db35ed111ca35

commit_message:
Fix and enable test_port_forwarding

This test began failing because of inconsistencies in the
in-memory neutron db that occur since the change
https://review.opendev.org/#/c/750295/ got merged.

The failure observed was that an entry in the port forwarding
table was created but never got added as a row. When the get
operation for the entry created happened, it raised a not found
exception. To avoid this situation the test will now use
OS_TEST_DBAPI_ADMIN_CONNECTION=sqlite:///sqlite.db

This reverts commit 481f0b3b3c6014c23b9619b6c361754d0185dce1.
Related-bug: #1894117
Closes-bug: #1896678
Co-Authored-By: Jakub Libosvar <libosvar@redhat.com>
Change-Id: Ic753232ee576fb8b663af5c4a68635bb40a40edc

Improve bearer auth handling

We can share tokens across threads for scope so if we are fetching
multiple layers of the same container, let's reuse the token rather than
duplicating the token request. Additionally we can verify if a token
needs to be refreshed based on the expiration time.

Note: python2 code was added to build the token variable.

Change-Id: I4a3149b08013f493e13b592f064e3ff2ed4074f7
(cherry picked from commit f52b1e1a46ef1c18593106d09e1eb5fff7d13917)

commit_message:
Bump py37 to py38 in tox.ini

Python 3.8 is now our highest level supported python runtime.
This updates the default tox target environments to swap out py37 for
py38 to make sure local development testing is covering this version.
This does not impact zuul jobs in any way, nor prevent local tests
against py37. It just changes the default if none is explicitly provided.

refer: https://governance.openstack.org/tc/reference/runtimes/victoria.html

Change-Id: Ie03be9269a5595a2c7c9e1fcfbe3ef04943280bd

commit_message:
Update TOX_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/victoria

Update the URL to the upper-constraints file to point to the redirect
rule on releases.openstack.org so that anyone working on this branch
will switch to the correct upper-constraints list automatically when
the requirements repository branches.

Until the requirements repository has as stable/victoria branch, tests will
continue to use the upper-constraints list on master.

Change-Id: I01fdd0e6c290b1b896e8c7e051af9867a55102db

commit_message:
test amphora stats role

Validates that users without the loadbalancer admin role cannot see the amphora statistics info

Change-Id: I3380299f3784918c5af143528f06043fb2b9cf50
git_command: git fetch https://review.opendev.org/openstack/octavia-tempest-plugin refs/changes/80/756980/4 && git format-patch -1 --stdout FETCH_HEAD
added_lines: @decorators.idempotent_id('e24bfd64-d94b-4824-97f9-262cd00c2759') def test_amphora_stats(self): """Tests amphora stats API. * Show the statistics for an amphora. * Validate the show reflects the requested values. * Validates that users without the loadbalancer admin role cannot see the amphora statistics info. """ # We have to do this here as the api_version and clients are not # setup in time to use a decorator or the skip_checks mixin if not self.lb_admin_amphora_client.is_version_supported( self.api_version, '2.3'): raise self.skipException('Amphora update is only available on ' 'Octavia API version 2.3 or newer.') # Get an actual list of the amphorae amphorae = self.lb_admin_amphora_client.list_amphorae( query_params='{loadbalancer_id}={lb_id}'.format( loadbalancer_id=const.LOADBALANCER_ID, lb_id=self.lb_id)) # Test that a user without the load balancer admin role cannot # see this amphora statistics info if CONF.load_balancer.RBAC_test_type == const.ADVANCED: self.assertRaises( exceptions.Forbidden, self.os_primary.amphora_client.update_amphora_config, amphorae[0][const.ID]) for amp in amphorae: # Verify the show reflects the requested values amphora_stats = self.lb_admin_amphora_client.get_amphora_stats( amphora_id=amp[const.ID]) for listener in amphora_stats: self.assertEqual(self.lb_id, listener[const.LOADBALANCER_ID]) self.assertEqual(amp[const.ID], listener[const.ID]) self.assertIn("active_connections", listener) self.assertIn("amphora_stats", listener) self.assertIn("bytes_in", listener) self.assertIn("bytes_out", listener) self.assertIn("listener_id", listener) self.assertIn("request_errors", listener) self.assertIn("total_connections", listener)

commit_message:
Update TOX_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/victoria

Update the URL to the upper-constraints file to point to the redirect
rule on releases.openstack.org so that anyone working on this branch
will switch to the correct upper-constraints list automatically when
the requirements repository branches.

Until the requirements repository has as stable/victoria branch, tests will
continue to use the upper-constraints list on master.

Change-Id: I780d499a5812d318fdd093bf8d824ef721fff80b

commit_message:
Bump default tox env from py37 to py38

Python 3.8 is now our highest level supported python runtime.
This updates the default tox target environments to swap out
py37 for py38 to make sure local development testing is
covering this version.

This does not impact zuul jobs in any way, nor prevent local
tests against py37. It just changes the default if none is
explicitly provided.

Change-Id: I2d5333478fdcc96b505bee0329b6a609201a5d92

commit_message:
Update TOX_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/victoria

Update the URL to the upper-constraints file to point to the redirect
rule on releases.openstack.org so that anyone working on this branch
will switch to the correct upper-constraints list automatically when
the requirements repository branches.

Until the requirements repository has as stable/victoria branch, tests will
continue to use the upper-constraints list on master.

Change-Id: Ieb27c8548c28cc4e85a658fd4c1530dd5881be74
